This paper deals with motion generation and control of humanoid robots, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses optimization techniques and models, which could be categorized under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of mixed integer programming and optimization of end-effector contacts location suggests that the paper could also be classified under control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper mentions experimental results and the use of computer vision, which could fall under computer vision (cs.CV).
